Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. In a small #pot{}, combine 1¼ cups @water{} (2¼ cups for 4 servings) and a pinch of @salt{}; bring to a boil. Mince or grate @garlic{2%cloves}. Peel and mince @ginger{1%inch} until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4). Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{3/4%cup} to pot. Cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve. Meanwhile, toss @broccoli{8%florets} on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until tender and crisped, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken fillets{12%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in a large #pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned, ~{5-7%minutes} per side (it'll cook through in the next step). Turn off heat; remove from pan and set aside. Wipe out pan.

While chicken cooks, in a small #bowl{}, whisk together ¼ cup @water{} (⅓ cup water for 4 servings), @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, @honey{2%tbsp}, and @soy sauce{2%tbsp} until very smooth. Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{} in pan used for chicken over medium-low heat. Add garlic, ginger, and scallion whites. Cook, stirring, until fragrant and slightly softened, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute}.

Pour half the @white wine vinegar{5%tsp} (use all for 4 servings) into pan and simmer until almost evaporated. Stir in sauce and bring to a boil. Let bubble until thickened, ~{30%seconds} to ~{1%minute} (1-2 minutes for 4). Stir in @sesame oil{1%tsp} (2 tsp for 4). Return chicken to pan and reduce heat to medium low; turn to coat in sauce. Continue cooking until sauce thickens and chicken is cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If sauce is too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Fluff rice with a #fork{} and season with @salt{}. Stir in 1 tsp remaining @sesame oil{1%tsp} (use all remaining sesame oil for 4 servings), then divide between plates. Top with chicken and add broccoli to the side. Spoon any remaining sauce over chicken. Garnish with scallion greens and @sesame seeds{}.